cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG

This paper deals with the satisfiability problem of a logic system that extends Propositional Dynamic Logic (PDL) to reason about types of actions and agent capabilities. This makes it relevant to several subfields of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the complexity of the satisfiability problem and presents a tableau-based algorithm, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
